{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Cupid enrichment op: LLM ticket-digest extractor + digest schema\n\n## Why\nSemantic overlap detection needs a compact, normalized per-ticket representation that catches paraphrase (\"login broken\" vs \"users can't authenticate\") WITHOUT embeddings or a vector DB — keeping rebar on its Anthropic-only, no-heavy-ML grain. The Cupid pattern (arXiv:2308.10022) uses the LLM as a one-time feature extractor: expensive semantics amortized per-ticket, cheap lexical match forever after.\n\n## What\nA new LLM operation `rebar.llm.enrich(ticket_id)` that reads a ticket's full text and returns a validated dedup digest, plus its output schema and prompt. Modeled on `src/rebar/llm/completion.py` / `src/rebar/llm/operations.py` (assemble context → load prompt → RunRequest(mode=\"structured\") → validate).\n\nDigest schema (register as `ticket_digest`): `{problem_keywords: string[], component_or_area: string, key_entities: string[], propositions: string[]}` where `propositions` holds `PROPOSITIONS_MIN..PROPOSITIONS_MAX` (default 2..6, exposed as config, see below) atomic problem/repro statements. Logs, stack traces, and code are discarded by the prompt. The op is deterministic/idempotent: no timestamps or nondeterministic fields in the payload, so re-extraction of identical input reproduces the digest byte-for-byte.\n\n## Scope (exact edit targets)\n- New op module `src/rebar/llm/enrich.py`; export `enrich` from `src/rebar/llm/__init__.py` (NOT `src/rebar/__init__.py` — LLM ops live under `rebar.llm`, mirroring `review_ticket`/`verify_completion`; core must not import `rebar.llm`).\n- Prompt file at the canonical location `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/enrich.md` (single location; not `.rebar/prompts/`) with front-matter `execution_mode: single_turn` (the valid enum is `single_turn|agentic` per `src/rebar/llm/prompting/prompts.py:74`; `1-TURN` is invalid and raises PromptError).\n- Output schema `src/rebar/schemas/ticket_digest.schema.json`; register the structured response model in `src/rebar/llm/contracts.py` via `register_contract(\"ticket_digest\", …)` so `mode=\"structured\"` binds it (otherwise it silently falls back to the findings model).\n- Config: add `PROPOSITIONS_MIN/MAX` to the typed config (`src/rebar/_config_schema.py`, a new `overlap`/`enrich` section) rather than hardcoding, so downstream S5/S6 can tune granularity.\n- OUT of scope: storage (S2 = wispy-cheerless-tick), queue (S3), drain (S4), retrieval/judge (S5/S6/S7).\n\n## Dependencies\nNone (this is the leaf the others build on). S2/S5/S7 consume this op and its `ticket_digest` schema.\n\n## Testing\n- Unit: `tests/unit/test_enrich.py` — idempotency (same input → identical payload), field presence/types against the schema, logs/code excluded, malformed-LLM-output handled (tolerant parse → clean error, no partial write), disabled/absent-LLM raises cleanly.\n- Eval: `.rebar/evals/enrich.eval.yaml` with INDEPENDENTLY hand-authored ground-truth (NOT prompt-output-as-oracle) on ≥6 representative tickets incl. epic-sized (~4000-token) bodies, asserting the digest names the core problem + ≥1 correct entity.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `rebar.llm.enrich(ticket_id)` returns a `ticket_digest`-schema-valid `{problem_keywords, component_or_area, key_entities, propositions}`; verified by `pytest tests/unit/test_enrich.py::test_schema_valid`.\n- [ ] Logs/stack-traces/code are excluded from the digest; verified by a fixture ticket containing a stack trace whose frames do not appear in the digest.\n- [ ] Idempotent: identical input text yields a byte-identical digest payload; verified by `pytest tests/unit/test_enrich.py::test_idempotent`.\n- [ ] Malformed structured LLM output is handled by the tolerant parse and reported as a clean error with no partial write; verified by a FakeRunner test returning bad JSON.\n- [ ] Disabled/absent-LLM path raises/reports cleanly (no partial writes) so callers can graceful-skip.\n- [ ] `propositions` count is bounded by the configurable `PROPOSITIONS_MIN/MAX` (default 2..6); the eval spec uses independently-authored ground truth (no self-oracle) on ≥6 tickets incl. ~4000-token bodies.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783571020341744001,"uuid":"d222a0e1-acba-44b1-b908-ec6f343c9eca"}